    <h1>in audible: The Baroque Cello Project</h1>

    <p>a celebration of the hidden, the underheard, the disregarded, the nevernoticed: the sounds, the silences, the stillnesses, and the subtleties of power always present in any act of thinking and making</p>

    <p>a unique evolving collaborative project based on the hand-crafting of a Baroque cello<br>
    a multi-layered performative sound-led audio/visual installation centering on the cello surrounded by the sounds of its own making</p>

    <p>this website follows the project from its start in October 2013, the premiere presentation in autumn 2014, and its further development presented in summer 2015</p>

    <p>since the successful completion of Part II funding has been sought to continue the project with developments that would incorporate cutting edge digital technology - cutting edge tech from three centuries ago playing with cutting edge tech from today. unfortunately this has been unsuccessful despite support from an arts venue.</p>

    <p>we remain optimistic that the project will continue in the future</p>
